FBIS4-59441 "drnes093_j_94014" FBIS-NES-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Oil Minister Visits Syria's al-Asad, Conveys Message Oil Minister Visits Syria's al-Asad, Conveys Message EA1205211794 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1800 GMT 12 May 94 EA1205211794 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Salih Abu-Bakr Bin-Husaynun, minister of oil and mineral resources, arrived in Damascus earlier today on a visit to Syria during which he will convey a message from brother 'Ali Salim al- Bid, vice chairman of the Presidential Council and secretary general of the Yemeni Socialist Party, to his brother Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad. The message concerns the incidents and developments in our country after the outbreak of war. Egyptian President Muhammad Husni Mubarak received brother Salih Bin-Husaynun this morning in Cairo. The Egyptian MIDDLE EAST NEWS AGENCY stated today that brother Bin-Husaynun had presented at the meeting, a full report on current events and military clashes in Yemen.
